<%#
  CZID-330 — export-control / Terms-of-Use attestation click-through.

  ⚠️ TODO(counsel): ALL user-facing copy on this page is a PLACEHOLDER. The attestation wording has legal
  weight and enforceability and MUST be drafted or approved by counsel before go-live (design doc §6,
  decision point #8). Do not treat the text below as final. When the copy changes, bump
  ExportControlAttestation::CURRENT_VERSION in lockstep so users re-attest.

  This is a minimal, dependency-free skeleton (no React/webpack entry) so the gate is functional now;
  the polished UI is a follow-up (see the PR description).
%>
<div class="export-control-attestation" style="max-width: 720px; margin: 64px auto; padding: 0 24px; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;">
  <h1 style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
    <%# TODO(counsel): heading copy %>
    Export-control acknowledgement required
  </h1>

  <div style="background:#f6f8fa; border:1px solid #d0d7de; border-radius:6px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:24px; line-height:1.6;">
    <p><strong>PLACEHOLDER — pending counsel-approved text (TODO(counsel)).</strong></p>
    <p>
      Access to this service is subject to U.S. export-control laws. By continuing, you attest that you
      are not located in, ordinarily resident in, or accessing this service on behalf of any individual
      or entity in a jurisdiction subject to U.S. export-control restrictions, and that you are not a
      restricted or denied party under applicable law.
    </p>
    <p>
      [The exact attestation language, the list of covered jurisdictions, and any required
      certifications are counsel-owned and will replace this placeholder before enforcement is enabled.]
    </p>
  </div>

  <%= form_with url: export_control_attestations_path, method: :post, local: true do %>
    <%# The version the user is agreeing to is recorded server-side; surfaced here for the record. %>
    <p style="color:#57606a; font-size:13px; margin-bottom:20px;">
      Attestation version: <%= @attestation_version %>
    </p>

    <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center;">
      <%# ACCEPT — records "accepted" and lets the user proceed. %>
      <button type="submit" name="decision" value="<%= ExportControlAttestation::DECISION_ACCEPTED %>"
              style="background:#0969da; color:#fff; border:none; border-radius:6px; padding:10px 20px; font-size:15px; cursor:pointer;">
        <%# TODO(counsel): button label %>
        I attest and agree — continue
      </button>

      <%# DECLINE — records "declined" and routes to the deny page. %>
      <button type="submit" name="decision" value="<%= ExportControlAttestation::DECISION_DECLINED %>"
              style="background:#fff; color:#cf222e; border:1px solid #cf222e; border-radius:6px; padding:10px 20px; font-size:15px; cursor:pointer;">
        <%# TODO(counsel): button label %>
        I do not agree
      </button>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
